duties_responsibilities.duty: Provide psychiatric nursing care to child and adolescent patients in a hospital setting during evening shifts for a 13-week assignment.
Utilize recent acute psych experience to assess, plan, implement, and evaluate patient care.
Collaborate with multidisciplinary team members to ensure the delivery of high-quality care.
Adhere to Minnesota RN licensing requirements and maintain good standing throughout the assignment.

education_certification.credential: Minnesota RN license in good standing with 2 or more years of recent acute psych experience
